WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.336 --> 00:00:03.869
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> The Bastard Executioner...

2
00:00:03.871 --> 00:00:06.171
(screaming)

3
00:00:06.673 --> 00:00:07.838
BERBER:
There are many things

4
00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:10.073
we do not know about our leader.

5
00:00:10.075 --> 00:00:11.340
Even Petra knows
little of his life

6
00:00:11.342 --> 00:00:13.175
<i>before he came to the river.</i>

7
00:00:13.177 --> 00:00:15.043
Will you ever
tell me what you see?

8
00:00:15.045 --> 00:00:16.911
ANGEL CHILD AND ANNORA:
Your savior needs you

9
00:00:16.913 --> 00:00:19.013
to live the life
of a different man.

10
00:00:19.015 --> 00:00:21.015
MAN:
Gawain Maddox!

11
00:00:21.017 --> 00:00:22.783
- The traveling punisher.
- Ah.

12
00:00:22.785 --> 00:00:24.885
This is half my wage.

13
00:00:24.887 --> 00:00:26.786
If you do not find this
satisfactory.

14
00:00:26.788 --> 00:00:28.154
move on.

15
00:00:28.156 --> 00:00:30.222
Time is a most
aggressive foe. Milus.

16
00:00:30.224 --> 00:00:31.723
I need to make my gains now.

17
00:00:31.725 --> 00:00:33.224
<i>We need to fortify</i>
<i>our resources.</i>

18
00:00:33.226 --> 00:00:35.859
<i>Steeper taxes and tariffs.</i>

19
00:00:35.861 --> 00:00:37.293
LADY LOVE:
You will break them. Milus.

20
00:00:37.295 --> 00:00:39.314
And we both know
there's nothing more dangerous

21
00:00:39.315 --> 00:00:41.305
than a Welshman
who has nothing to lose.

22
00:00:41.308 --> 00:00:42.464
Tell me. Baroness.

23
00:00:42.765 --> 00:00:44.898
<i>How is it that someone</i>
<i>of your privilege</i>

24
00:00:44.900 --> 00:00:47.734
<i>may come to know</i>
<i>the plight of the common man?</i>

25
00:00:47.736 --> 00:00:49.936
It is time.

26
00:00:49.938 --> 00:00:50.924
TORAN:
Brother Wilk.

27
00:00:51.006 --> 00:00:52.804
- Ventris comes again.
- Already?

28
00:00:53.004 --> 00:00:55.840
JACOB: They'll take what little
stock and harvest we have left.

29
00:00:55.842 --> 00:00:57.341
We can't do this without you.

30
00:00:57.343 --> 00:00:59.176
Yea.

31
00:00:59.178 --> 00:01:01.605
Gather supplies. We'll need
to ride before midday.

32
00:01:01.705 --> 00:01:03.733
PETRA:
<i>You're not a rebel. Wilkin.</i>

33
00:01:03.849 --> 00:01:05.782
- JONAS:<i> Took us in darkness.</i>
- (laughter)

34
00:01:05.784 --> 00:01:06.749
Deadly ghosts.

35
00:01:06.751 --> 00:01:07.983
<i>In familiar hoods.</i>

36
00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:10.652
<i>There was another this time.
Saw a flash of his face.</i>

37
00:01:10.654 --> 00:01:13.121
PETRA:
<i>Ventris is sly and brutal.</i>

38
00:01:13.123 --> 00:01:15.523
It's only time and chance
before you feel his blade.

39
00:01:15.525 --> 00:01:18.758
- We've barely stock and food to live.
- You're the only stock

40
00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:20.117
I can't live without!

41
00:01:20.862 --> 00:01:23.863
Is there a mind for fairness
in your swift purpose?

42
00:01:23.865 --> 00:01:25.197
Of course. my love.

43
00:01:25.199 --> 00:01:27.365
Fair process for every man.

44
00:01:27.367 --> 00:01:28.632
We can't do this alone anymore.

45
00:01:28.634 --> 00:01:30.600
<i>You saw the daffodil hides</i>
<i>in the trees.</i>

46
00:01:30.602 --> 00:01:32.001
The Byth Encil rebels

47
00:01:32.003 --> 00:01:33.296
would welcome our skill.

48
00:01:33.496 --> 00:01:36.176
VENTRIS: Where are your men?!

49
00:01:36.273 --> 00:01:37.505
They went to Glen Darby Birch.

50
00:01:37.607 --> 00:01:40.340
- With their hoods?
- Yea! With hoods!

51
00:01:40.342 --> 00:01:43.308
(Eva screaming)

52
00:01:44.111 --> 00:01:45.871
VENTRIS:
<i>Kill them all.</i>

53
00:01:46.179 --> 00:01:47.444
<i>Burn it to the ground.</i>

54
00:01:49.347 --> 00:01:51.413
What are you...?

55
00:02:00.390 --> 00:02:03.490
- (fire crackling)
- _

56
00:02:06.827 --> 00:02:07.826
(shouts)

57
00:02:08.301 --> 00:02:09.968
- (groans)
- Careful. boy.

58
00:02:10.069 --> 00:02:13.005
S-Sorry. Ma.
(groans)

59
00:02:18.411 --> 00:02:21.479
It's shit. Hmm?

60
00:02:21.581 --> 00:02:23.380
Like the lot of you.

61
00:02:23.481 --> 00:02:25.817
- Come here.
- I'm-I'm sorry.

62
00:02:25.918 --> 00:02:28.218
- (baby crying)
- Don't mother him.

63
00:02:28.319 --> 00:02:31.188
He needs to feel the pain
of his mistake.

64
00:02:31.288 --> 00:02:33.023
JESSAMY:
He feels it.

65
00:02:33.124 --> 00:02:35.859
I won't tend it.

66
00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:39.229
Please. enjoy the drink.

67
00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:41.098
We have another bird.

68
00:02:41.199 --> 00:02:42.933
I'll feed you in short.

69
00:02:43.034 --> 00:02:45.301
- Don't put rule on me. whore!
- (groans)

70
00:02:47.104 --> 00:02:48.738
No.
(crying)

71
00:02:48.839 --> 00:02:50.039
Crawl. you cur!

72
00:02:50.140 --> 00:02:51.641
JESSAMY:
Please. Maddy.

73
00:02:51.742 --> 00:02:53.443
GAWAIN:
Show me the trench.

74
00:03:00.016 --> 00:03:01.417
The village!

75
00:03:01.518 --> 00:03:03.819
Hyah!
(shouts)

76
00:03:08.291 --> 00:03:09.658
(horse neighs)

77
00:03:18.167 --> 00:03:20.769
(Wilkin groans)

78
00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:23.472
(shuddering breaths)

79
00:03:23.573 --> 00:03:24.773
No.

80
00:03:24.874 --> 00:03:27.441
(panting)

81
00:03:27.542 --> 00:03:29.510
No.

82
00:03:29.611 --> 00:03:31.545
(crying)

83
00:03:36.851 --> 00:03:39.052
(crying)

84
00:03:58.773 --> 00:04:00.774
(panting)

85
00:04:08.916 --> 00:04:11.550
(crying softly)

86
00:04:11.651 --> 00:04:13.385
Dear child.

87
00:04:19.659 --> 00:04:21.093
(panting)

88
00:04:26.598 --> 00:04:28.599
Oh...

89
00:04:43.316 --> 00:04:45.283
(sobs)

90
00:04:45.384 --> 00:04:47.684
Sweet boy.

91
00:04:52.190 --> 00:04:54.524
My Rhys.

92
00:04:59.264 --> 00:05:01.665
This was Ventris.

93
00:05:01.766 --> 00:05:04.001
His collector as proof!

94
00:05:04.102 --> 00:05:06.503
Savage noble!

95
00:05:12.276 --> 00:05:14.845
Damn your holy destiny.

96
00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:22.252
(sobbing):
Devil Christ. Damn you.

97
00:05:44.408 --> 00:05:46.409
(grunting)

98
00:06:00.356 --> 00:06:02.357
(panting)

99
00:06:11.901 --> 00:06:13.902
(grunts)

100
00:06:17.139 --> 00:06:18.873
JACOB:
The sword.

101
00:06:21.043 --> 00:06:23.545
Crest of Edward the First.

102
00:06:28.015 --> 00:06:29.416
(grunts)

103
00:06:29.517 --> 00:06:31.485
CALO:
Where does he ride?

104
00:06:31.586 --> 00:06:33.554
To meet the devil.

105
00:06:33.655 --> 00:06:36.022
As are we.

106
00:06:36.123 --> 00:06:37.758
Our families...

107
00:06:37.859 --> 00:06:39.760
Will be avenged.

108
00:06:39.861 --> 00:06:41.662
- (horse neighs)
- Hup!

109
00:06:41.763 --> 00:06:43.697
(grunts)

110
00:06:54.908 --> 00:06:57.177
See to the dead.

111
00:06:57.278 --> 00:06:58.744
This is my fight.

112
00:06:58.846 --> 00:07:01.481
We've all earned this horror.

113
00:07:06.286 --> 00:07:09.822
I've no plan but vengeance.

114
00:07:09.923 --> 00:07:12.492
The only plan left.

115
00:07:24.037 --> 00:07:25.604
Yea. then.

116
00:07:25.705 --> 00:07:27.438
To Castle Ventris.

117
00:07:27.540 --> 00:07:29.040
- (horse neighs)
- Ha!

118
00:07:31.978 --> 00:07:33.979
(shouting)

119
00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:58.569
This is mine.

120
00:07:58.670 --> 00:08:00.604
(shuddering breaths)

121
00:08:03.208 --> 00:08:04.909
My due.

122
00:08:05.010 --> 00:08:08.046
My sorrow.

123
00:08:13.152 --> 00:08:15.362
Forgive me.

124
00:08:17.989 --> 00:08:19.990
(sizzling. quiet gasping)

125
00:08:24.395 --> 00:08:26.396
(panting. sobbing)

126
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:34.950
♪ Born with a heart ♪

127
00:08:35.528 --> 00:08:40.871
♪ That could ache
more than beat ♪

128
00:08:42.923 --> 00:08:48.793
♪ The mind of a killer ♪

129
00:08:48.845 --> 00:08:52.630
♪ The soul of the meek ♪

130
00:08:55.185 --> 00:09:00.805
♪ Flock with no shepherd ♪

131
00:09:00.857 --> 00:09:06.911
♪ Is a vulnerable game ♪

132
00:09:06.980 --> 00:09:09.814
♪ I can live without a hearth ♪

133
00:09:09.866 --> 00:09:13.151
♪ Without love ♪

134
00:09:13.203 --> 00:09:17.205
♪ But I do need a name ♪

135
00:09:19.960 --> 00:09:22.544
♪ Father. do you burn ♪

136
00:09:22.629 --> 00:09:26.047
♪ If your hand is in fire? ♪

137
00:09:26.132 --> 00:09:29.133
♪ Does your head
spin with rage ♪

138
00:09:29.202 --> 00:09:32.637
♪ When fooled by the liars? ♪

139
00:09:32.706 --> 00:09:38.243
♪ King of the kings ♪

140
00:09:38.311 --> 00:09:42.897
♪ Do you feel any pain? ♪

141
00:09:44.484 --> 00:09:47.233
♪ Do you feel any pain? ♪

