144
00:10:00.765 --> 00:10:05.365
_

145
00:10:08.592 --> 00:10:11.027
The witch.

146
00:10:18.369 --> 00:10:20.336
What brings you so far east.

147
00:10:20.437 --> 00:10:22.171
woman?

148
00:10:22.273 --> 00:10:25.141
The same thing
that brings all of you.

149
00:10:25.242 --> 00:10:27.410
We flee the darkness.

150
00:10:27.511 --> 00:10:29.979
Did you witness the massacre?

151
00:10:30.080 --> 00:10:31.981
No.

152
00:10:32.082 --> 00:10:36.351
But I will witness yours
unless you alter your purpose.

153
00:10:36.452 --> 00:10:39.321
There's nothing to alter.

154
00:10:39.422 --> 00:10:41.055
We face what's ahead.

155
00:10:41.157 --> 00:10:45.994
But you do not need
to face it alone.

156
00:10:46.095 --> 00:10:50.599
Your cynic... he has ties
to the way of victory.

157
00:11:00.709 --> 00:11:04.245
You are all knots and coil.

158
00:11:04.346 --> 00:11:05.746
(inhales)

159
00:11:05.848 --> 00:11:08.582
Pain of yesterday's
fierce effort.

160
00:11:08.684 --> 00:11:10.018
(sighs softly)

161
00:11:12.021 --> 00:11:14.422
So you found your bandits.

162
00:11:14.523 --> 00:11:16.390
No.

163
00:11:16.491 --> 00:11:19.327
But we met with the
proof of their guilt.

164
00:11:21.330 --> 00:11:23.297
And you've returned
with that proof?

165
00:11:23.398 --> 00:11:25.899
(chuckles)

166
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:28.803
Difficult to carry
bone and slag.

167
00:11:28.903 --> 00:11:30.037
(door opens)

168
00:11:30.138 --> 00:11:32.139
CORBETT:
My lord.

169
00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:34.375
A scout came through from
midshire this morning.

170
00:11:34.476 --> 00:11:37.109
Spotted seven men
traveling east last night.

171
00:11:37.211 --> 00:11:39.946
One with a sword
bearing Longshanks' mark.

172
00:11:40.047 --> 00:11:41.948
Our bandits on a
mission. perhaps.

173
00:11:42.049 --> 00:11:44.384
Taking their vengeance
to my gate?

174
00:11:44.485 --> 00:11:46.820
Are they that mad with grief?

175
00:11:46.920 --> 00:11:50.323
Or soldiers willing to die
in service of their sorrow.

176
00:11:50.424 --> 00:11:52.492
I think it best
we meet them in journey.

177
00:11:52.593 --> 00:11:55.829
away from anyone who may see
this fool play as valiant.

178
00:11:55.929 --> 00:11:57.263
Stay.

179
00:11:57.365 --> 00:11:59.432
Protect the walls.

180
00:11:59.533 --> 00:12:01.166
Prepare a full legion
of foot soldiers.

181
00:12:01.267 --> 00:12:03.435
I'll gut this warrior bandit.

182
00:12:03.536 --> 00:12:06.137
Choke him cold with a snare
of his own entrails.

183
00:12:06.239 --> 00:12:08.173
A fine plan. my lord.

184
00:12:11.878 --> 00:12:14.279
Are you waiting
for a royal proclamation?

185
00:12:14.381 --> 00:12:15.947
Go with him. Reeve.

186
00:12:16.048 --> 00:12:18.216
Yes. indeed.
Chamberlain.

187
00:12:18.317 --> 00:12:19.651
My lady.

188
00:12:28.861 --> 00:12:30.862
(horses neighing)

189
00:12:44.043 --> 00:12:46.378
Who are you. traveler?

190
00:12:46.478 --> 00:12:48.379
Gawain Maddox. milord.

191
00:12:48.479 --> 00:12:50.114
I come up from the South.

192
00:12:50.215 --> 00:12:51.949
Punisher by trade.

193
00:12:52.050 --> 00:12:53.984
You have tools in possession?

194
00:12:54.085 --> 00:12:55.552
Yea'on.

195
00:12:55.653 --> 00:12:56.987
Ride with us.

196
00:12:57.088 --> 00:12:59.623
I may need your services.

197
00:12:59.724 --> 00:13:01.892
My family.

198
00:13:01.993 --> 00:13:03.394
Ride the main trail north.

199
00:13:03.494 --> 00:13:05.329
It leads to Castle Ventris.

200
00:13:05.430 --> 00:13:07.364
They can wait there.

201
00:13:09.366 --> 00:13:11.334
Just follow on.

202
00:13:11.435 --> 00:13:13.369
I'll be with you.

203
00:13:19.843 --> 00:13:21.844
(horses sputtering)

204
00:13:34.891 --> 00:13:38.727
Do you remember me.
Earl Constable?

205
00:13:40.764 --> 00:13:42.765
I'm the knight
you sent to his death

206
00:13:42.866 --> 00:13:46.068
at the hands
of the hoarding Scots.

207
00:13:47.102 --> 00:13:49.003
Impossible.

208
00:13:49.104 --> 00:13:52.573
You know this man. my lord?

209
00:13:52.675 --> 00:13:55.943
If you are indeed that knight.

210
00:13:56.045 --> 00:13:59.613
you're either a
deserter or a ghost.

211
00:13:59.715 --> 00:14:02.984
If not dead then.

212
00:14:03.085 --> 00:14:05.019
then dead now.

213
00:14:10.758 --> 00:14:14.695
I live with the terror
of your betrayal every day.

214
00:14:17.499 --> 00:14:21.435
But I'll spare you that pain.

215
00:14:21.536 --> 00:14:24.371
Death will quiet your mind.

216
00:14:33.480 --> 00:14:35.548
They're all rebels. milord.

217
00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:41.254
Time to go back to hell.
Marcher Baron!

218
00:14:42.156 --> 00:14:43.456
(whistles)

219
00:14:43.557 --> 00:14:44.724
(horses neighing)

220
00:14:47.895 --> 00:14:50.830
<i>Deus vult!</i>

221
00:14:50.931 --> 00:14:52.364
(men shouting)

222
00:15:15.821 --> 00:15:17.789
(yells)

223
00:15:47.184 --> 00:15:48.350
Go. go. go!

224
00:15:52.055 --> 00:15:53.555
(screams)

225
00:15:57.294 --> 00:15:59.162
(neighs)

226
00:16:18.080 --> 00:16:19.414
(grunts)

227
00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:36.897
(screams)

228
00:17:07.961 --> 00:17:11.897
Not ghost. nor deserter.

229
00:17:11.998 --> 00:17:14.766
Nor hood.

230
00:17:20.638 --> 00:17:22.306
(yells)

231
00:17:30.849 --> 00:17:32.416
(yells)

232
00:17:39.490 --> 00:17:40.523
(yells)

233
00:17:53.738 --> 00:17:55.437
VENTRIS:
London will hunt down

234
00:17:55.538 --> 00:17:58.975
the hooded bandits
and crush your toy rebellion.

235
00:17:59.076 --> 00:18:01.110
I've no rebellion.

236
00:18:01.211 --> 00:18:02.979
Just a need to see you die.

237
00:18:06.617 --> 00:18:07.650
(yells)

238
00:18:25.268 --> 00:18:27.269
♪

239
00:18:59.417 --> 00:19:02.019
How is he?
Will he heal?

240
00:19:02.120 --> 00:19:05.856
Only blood runs.
no other humors.

241
00:19:05.957 --> 00:19:07.891
He will sleep.

242
00:19:15.899 --> 00:19:18.034
BERBER:
Ventris was right.

243
00:19:18.135 --> 00:19:19.568
The king's army

244
00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:23.539
will come. hunt down
the hooded thieves.

245
00:19:23.641 --> 00:19:26.909
Yea. No rock unturned until our shit
holes are split on the cradle.

246
00:19:27.011 --> 00:19:27.944
Mm.

247
00:19:29.779 --> 00:19:32.213
Your. uh...

248
00:19:32.315 --> 00:19:35.250
your dark friend...
is he. um...

249
00:19:35.351 --> 00:19:36.952
in our pope's grace?

250
00:19:37.053 --> 00:19:39.921
A moor. converted
in his homeland.

251
00:19:42.091 --> 00:19:44.225
A good Catholic like us all.

252
00:19:45.461 --> 00:19:48.463
Yea. Bloody work
is the Lord's.

253
00:19:48.564 --> 00:19:49.797
TORAN:
Indeed.

254
00:19:52.701 --> 00:19:54.835
I need a name
to offer my thanks.

255
00:19:54.936 --> 00:19:56.503
Gruffudd.

256
00:19:56.604 --> 00:19:59.373
You're the one
they call "the wolf."

257
00:19:59.474 --> 00:20:01.341
I'm called many hard things.

258
00:20:01.442 --> 00:20:02.777
Most by my wife.

259
00:20:02.878 --> 00:20:05.412
Thank you for answering
our plea. Gruffudd.

260
00:20:05.513 --> 00:20:07.081
We serve each other. friend.

261
00:20:07.182 --> 00:20:09.549
The baron's forged weapons
will be a welcome change

262
00:20:09.651 --> 00:20:11.618
from our sticks
and cobbled blades.

263
00:20:11.719 --> 00:20:13.487
Ventris has lost
nearly two legions.

264
00:20:13.588 --> 00:20:14.822
His army is weakened.

265
00:20:14.923 --> 00:20:16.556
We're not ready to storm walls.

266
00:20:16.658 --> 00:20:18.159
Even with noble swords.

267
00:20:18.260 --> 00:20:22.095
But word of this victory
will spread and it will inspire.

268
00:20:22.196 --> 00:20:23.429
Our numbers will grow.

269
00:20:23.530 --> 00:20:25.165
I have no doubt.

270
00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:28.434
Godspeed for your knight's
return to sound body.

271
00:20:28.535 --> 00:20:30.736
An unlikely ally in our fight.

272
00:20:30.838 --> 00:20:32.738
Let him know there
may come a time

273
00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:34.540
when I collect on this favor.

274
00:20:43.750 --> 00:20:45.851
Toran. Moor!

275
00:20:51.825 --> 00:20:53.392
You crazy witch!

276
00:21:00.099 --> 00:21:01.500
To what end

277
00:21:01.601 --> 00:21:03.536
does this devilry serve?

278
00:21:06.939 --> 00:21:08.940
(grunting)

279
00:21:17.783 --> 00:21:19.751
The baron has returned?

280
00:21:19.852 --> 00:21:22.754
No. But I have
news of his need.

281
00:21:22.855 --> 00:21:24.956
At Heaven's Eye.
we saw the rebel symbols.

282
00:21:25.057 --> 00:21:28.326
Lord Ventris sent me back
to secure more troops.

283
00:21:30.161 --> 00:21:32.629
Sent you back? Alone?

284
00:21:32.731 --> 00:21:34.398
Not to spare arms he may need.

285
00:21:34.499 --> 00:21:36.433
I welcomed the risk
of riding apart.

286
00:21:48.212 --> 00:21:50.748
Gather what men we can spare.

287
00:21:50.849 --> 00:21:52.516
With haste.

288
00:21:56.153 --> 00:21:58.021
Shall I find the baroness?

289
00:21:58.122 --> 00:22:01.024
No. You should find a bath.

290
00:22:01.125 --> 00:22:03.693
You reek of shit.

291
00:22:03.794 --> 00:22:05.195
And fear.

292
00:22:22.078 --> 00:22:24.079
(sighs)

293
00:22:49.138 --> 00:22:51.139
(groans)

294
00:22:56.746 --> 00:22:59.547
You join the living.

295
00:22:59.648 --> 00:23:01.248
Who did this?

296
00:23:01.349 --> 00:23:03.451
The healer.

297
00:23:03.552 --> 00:23:05.486
She offered no reason.

298
00:23:12.961 --> 00:23:14.361
(groans)

299
00:23:35.716 --> 00:23:37.717
Cut her binds.

300
00:23:51.198 --> 00:23:53.665
Why did you cut and scar me?

301
00:23:53.766 --> 00:23:56.469
To save you.

302
00:23:56.569 --> 00:23:58.904
Your only chance

303
00:23:59.005 --> 00:24:01.707
to live is to be supposed dead.

304
00:24:04.043 --> 00:24:06.077
He gives you that gift.

305
00:24:24.497 --> 00:24:26.964
Who are you. woman?

306
00:24:27.066 --> 00:24:28.799
Truly.

307
00:24:28.901 --> 00:24:31.836
What's your interest in me?

308
00:24:34.340 --> 00:24:37.842
You have a fate...

309
00:24:37.943 --> 00:24:39.877
that you must learn to hold.

310
00:24:39.978 --> 00:24:44.849
One that will forever
mark your place in time.

311
00:24:46.885 --> 00:24:49.554
I am here to help
tell that story.

312
00:24:51.590 --> 00:24:53.625
My story is over.

313
00:24:53.726 --> 00:24:55.526
No.

314
00:24:55.628 --> 00:24:58.963
It is just begun.

315
00:24:59.064 --> 00:25:02.098
The angel spoke the truth.

316
00:25:06.137 --> 00:25:08.338
The angel?

317
00:25:08.439 --> 00:25:11.575
The bright child
who came to you.

318
00:25:13.411 --> 00:25:15.078
How...

319
00:25:17.081 --> 00:25:21.117
I've never whispered
a word of that to anyone.

320
00:25:23.154 --> 00:25:25.922
I hear the same voices.

321
00:25:29.426 --> 00:25:33.296
It's time to lay down
this sword. Wilkin Brattle.

322
00:25:34.899 --> 00:25:37.033
(angel child's voice):
Your savior needs you

323
00:25:37.134 --> 00:25:40.303
to live the life
of a different man.

324
00:26:11.975 --> 00:26:13.975
Unhitch one of the
horses. brother.

325
00:26:14.076 --> 00:26:16.444
Then go join the
others at the caves.

326
00:26:16.545 --> 00:26:20.181
I think I'll finish
the ride. friend.

327
00:26:20.282 --> 00:26:22.884
A plan hatched by a witch...
what's to worry?

328
00:26:24.887 --> 00:26:29.490
We deliver the dead. tell
the tale. and ride off.

329
00:26:29.592 --> 00:26:32.159
Free men. no price on our head.

330
00:26:32.260 --> 00:26:34.027
It's a sound devise.

331
00:26:34.129 --> 00:26:36.563
Simple enough an executioner
could carry it forth.

332
00:26:36.663 --> 00:26:38.565
(chuckles)

333
00:26:38.665 --> 00:26:40.733
And what say of your purpose.

334
00:26:40.834 --> 00:26:44.404
What name for you?
Sneermonger?

335
00:26:46.474 --> 00:26:50.410
Well. my da. he wanted
to call me Marshal.

336
00:26:50.511 --> 00:26:53.113
But my ma thought it
too destined to war.

337
00:26:53.214 --> 00:26:56.015
Ma got the name.
da got the destiny.

338
00:26:56.117 --> 00:26:58.050
Yea. indeed.

339
00:26:58.151 --> 00:27:00.052
And what of your father?

340
00:27:00.153 --> 00:27:02.088
You never tell of anything.

341
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:08.094
There's nothing to tell.
I don't have one.

342
00:27:10.897 --> 00:27:12.297
(grunts)

343
00:27:14.735 --> 00:27:17.469
(children's choir
singing Latin hymn)

344
00:27:29.882 --> 00:27:32.283
(choir continues
singing Latin hymn)

345
00:27:51.569 --> 00:27:53.236
(choir continues)

346
00:27:53.337 --> 00:27:54.738
ISABEL:
Pardon. Baroness.

347
00:27:54.839 --> 00:27:56.206
(choir stops singing)

348
00:27:56.307 --> 00:27:57.841
Outsiders have come.

349
00:27:57.942 --> 00:27:59.276
They bring sad news.

350
00:28:14.457 --> 00:28:16.458
Bring him down.

351
00:28:53.295 --> 00:28:56.431
My deepest condolences.
Lady Love.

352
00:28:56.532 --> 00:28:58.800
Let's bring you and the baron
into the castle

353
00:28:58.901 --> 00:29:00.835
so you can mourn in peace.

354
00:29:11.412 --> 00:29:14.749
Have the baron taken
to the sacrament room.

355
00:29:25.159 --> 00:29:27.493
Who are you?

356
00:29:30.497 --> 00:29:32.498
Gawain Maddox. milady.

357
00:29:32.599 --> 00:29:36.535
Punisher by trade.
from the southern land.

358
00:29:36.637 --> 00:29:38.537
This is Marshal.

359
00:29:38.639 --> 00:29:43.341
a journey soldier... he aids me
in the capture of the accused.

360
00:29:43.442 --> 00:29:45.778
Tell me of his death.

361
00:29:45.879 --> 00:29:48.947
We met the baron
at Heaven's Eye.

362
00:29:49.048 --> 00:29:50.949
Called upon us
to ride with him.

363
00:29:51.050 --> 00:29:52.550
At the grass fields.

364
00:29:52.652 --> 00:29:54.787
they crossed a band
of hooded thieves.

365
00:29:54.888 --> 00:29:56.221
Took a fierce run.

366
00:29:56.322 --> 00:29:58.857
Noblemen cut down
the seven of them.

367
00:29:58.958 --> 00:30:01.025
WILKIN:
Before the baron could rally.

368
00:30:01.126 --> 00:30:02.927
rebels attacked.

369
00:30:03.028 --> 00:30:05.263
50 or more.

370
00:30:05.363 --> 00:30:08.900
Caught the ranks tired
and out of formation.

371
00:30:09.001 --> 00:30:12.937
Your husband fought gallantly.
but the numbers were too steep.

372
00:30:14.339 --> 00:30:15.973
I'm sorry.

373
00:30:20.111 --> 00:30:21.945
Old men and boys.

374
00:30:22.046 --> 00:30:24.314
WILKIN: Your mail-clad soldiers
were too heavy to carry.

375
00:30:26.383 --> 00:30:29.085
We can send troops there
to collect the others.

376
00:30:29.187 --> 00:30:32.088
LADY LOVE: And what brings
an executioner to Ventrishire?

377
00:30:32.190 --> 00:30:33.990
Work. milady.

378
00:30:34.091 --> 00:30:36.026
I travel. go where
my services are needed.

379
00:30:36.127 --> 00:30:38.061
RANDULF:
He lies!

380
00:30:40.163 --> 00:30:41.931
This man is
not the executioner.

381
00:30:44.034 --> 00:30:45.868
He's one of the thieves.

382
00:30:45.969 --> 00:30:47.402
As is that one.

383
00:30:47.503 --> 00:30:50.339
You're the liar. sir.

384
00:30:50.440 --> 00:30:53.575
I've traveled with Gawain
for many years.

385
00:30:53.676 --> 00:30:56.145
Dispatch a messenger
to Glamorgan for proof.

386
00:30:56.246 --> 00:30:59.047
There is no other face
looks like this one.

387
00:30:59.148 --> 00:31:01.249
WILKIN:
We just came

388
00:31:01.350 --> 00:31:03.218
to deliver the dead.

389
00:31:03.319 --> 00:31:05.253
Out of respect.

390
00:31:05.354 --> 00:31:07.222
We'll leave if it upsets
your court.

391
00:31:07.323 --> 00:31:10.725
You'll stay and be quartered.

392
00:31:10.826 --> 00:31:14.062
The remedy for this dispute
is already here.

393
00:31:15.564 --> 00:31:17.698
The wife and children
of Maddox. sent here

394
00:31:17.799 --> 00:31:19.933
to wait for his return.

395
00:31:23.505 --> 00:31:25.840
Come forward.

396
00:31:28.744 --> 00:31:31.144
Tell us the truth.

397
00:31:31.246 --> 00:31:33.581
Is this man indeed your husband?

398
00:31:53.300 --> 00:31:55.301
(fussing)

399
00:32:01.173 --> 00:32:02.974
(trembling breaths)

400
00:32:03.075 --> 00:32:05.010
(whispers):
I'm sorry.

401
00:32:11.718 --> 00:32:13.719
My love.

402
00:32:16.255 --> 00:32:19.424
Good Maddy. thank God
you've come back safe.

403
00:32:24.196 --> 00:32:25.997
This is lunacy!

404
00:32:26.098 --> 00:32:28.566
She conspires with him!

405
00:32:32.805 --> 00:32:35.672
Such tragedy...

406
00:32:35.773 --> 00:32:38.142
lands on my name this day.

407
00:32:43.982 --> 00:32:45.515
My dearest friend.

408
00:32:45.616 --> 00:32:48.953
a life snuffed...

409
00:32:49.054 --> 00:32:51.488
not in a fitting battle...

410
00:32:52.757 --> 00:32:55.959
but by the ambush
of painted dogs.

411
00:32:58.462 --> 00:33:01.831
And my kin.

412
00:33:01.932 --> 00:33:04.733
Caught between two tales.

413
00:33:04.835 --> 00:33:06.635
I speak only truth.
dear brother.

414
00:33:06.736 --> 00:33:09.305
I have nothing to gain
from such a lie.

415
00:33:09.406 --> 00:33:11.507
These men are
the bandits we pursued.

416
00:33:11.608 --> 00:33:13.509
Did battle in the
fields beyond the eye.

417
00:33:13.610 --> 00:33:16.512
I myself
and other honored knights

418
00:33:16.613 --> 00:33:18.614
heard you tell
how you were dispatched

419
00:33:18.715 --> 00:33:21.183
<i>before</i> any such fray.

420
00:33:24.988 --> 00:33:26.455
Yea.

421
00:33:26.556 --> 00:33:28.824
- I did. but...
WILKIN: - You may have

422
00:33:28.925 --> 00:33:32.443
nothing to gain. but
you've much to hide.

423
00:33:32.528 --> 00:33:36.098
We saw this man at the fray.

424
00:33:36.199 --> 00:33:39.101
He tucked tail and slithered
away. letting his brothers

425
00:33:39.202 --> 00:33:41.389
fall to the curs.

426
00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:44.073
That's why he lies.

427
00:33:44.174 --> 00:33:45.575
'Cause we know the truth.

428
00:33:45.676 --> 00:33:47.009
That's...

429
00:33:47.110 --> 00:33:49.044
- I tell you. these are the...
CORBETT: - Enough!

430
00:34:00.590 --> 00:34:03.258
So. then. Reeve...

431
00:34:03.359 --> 00:34:06.561
you are either a false accuser

432
00:34:06.662 --> 00:34:08.963
or you deserted your commander
in battle!

433
00:34:10.965 --> 00:34:13.834
Both come with
a punishment of death!

434
00:34:15.970 --> 00:34:18.439
(whispering):
Please...

435
00:34:18.540 --> 00:34:20.341
Milus...

436
00:34:20.442 --> 00:34:21.908
brother...

437
00:34:22.009 --> 00:34:23.444
do not do this.

438
00:34:24.045 --> 00:34:25.511
Take him!

439
00:34:25.613 --> 00:34:27.180
Brother. we are blood.

440
00:34:27.281 --> 00:34:28.914
Do not betray me.
Damn you!

441
00:34:29.015 --> 00:34:30.415
Damn your half-hatred!

442
00:34:30.516 --> 00:34:31.583
Damn y...

443
00:34:31.684 --> 00:34:32.417
(grunts)

444
00:34:32.518 --> 00:34:34.453
(gasping)

445
00:34:34.554 --> 00:34:36.222
(Randulf yells)

446
00:34:36.322 --> 00:34:38.958
I'm gonna speak to the King!

447
00:34:39.059 --> 00:34:40.325
Curse you!

448
00:34:40.426 --> 00:34:41.861
I'll curse you from hell!

449
00:34:41.962 --> 00:34:43.729
(Randulf sobbing)

450
00:34:51.837 --> 00:34:55.240
My shame is only
outdone by my sadness.

451
00:34:57.276 --> 00:35:00.544
My deepest sympathies. Baroness.

452
00:35:00.646 --> 00:35:04.015
I am in your service.
whatever the need.

453
00:35:05.617 --> 00:35:07.751
Thank you. Milus.

454
00:35:09.821 --> 00:35:12.722
I will do haste
with manor law and trial.

455
00:35:14.826 --> 00:35:16.526
It is fitting...

456
00:35:16.627 --> 00:35:18.628
that the man falsely accused

457
00:35:18.729 --> 00:35:22.266
be the one who is skilled
to take his head.

458
00:35:33.677 --> 00:35:37.113
Welcome to Castle Ventris.
executioner.

459
00:36:12.210 --> 00:36:14.444
Baroness.

460
00:36:14.745 --> 00:36:17.480
The priest. he said I could
come for evening prayer.

461
00:36:17.581 --> 00:36:18.982
Please. sit.

462
00:36:18.983 --> 00:36:20.951
I welcome the chapel's use.

463
00:36:21.052 --> 00:36:23.854
Few spend time here but me.

464
00:36:27.592 --> 00:36:29.593
Do you mind?

465
00:36:31.495 --> 00:36:33.129
Please.

466
00:36:42.172 --> 00:36:44.173
I wouldn't think

467
00:36:44.275 --> 00:36:47.711
one of your trade would
complicate things with prayer.

468
00:36:50.248 --> 00:36:53.550
Perhaps it takes you in deeper.

469
00:36:58.489 --> 00:37:01.390
May I ask how this happened?

470
00:37:03.560 --> 00:37:05.861
It was given to me by a healer.

471
00:37:05.962 --> 00:37:09.030
A holy woman.

472
00:37:09.132 --> 00:37:11.433
A reminder
of my need for faith.

473
00:37:13.936 --> 00:37:16.037
Your soldier gave
the impression

474
00:37:16.139 --> 00:37:17.973
it distinguished
you for some time.

475
00:37:18.074 --> 00:37:21.543
Yet. the burn looks fresh.

476
00:37:21.645 --> 00:37:24.313
I renew the vow
when my faith wavers.

477
00:37:28.317 --> 00:37:30.718
You're bleeding.

478
00:37:30.820 --> 00:37:33.121
Yea.

479
00:37:33.222 --> 00:37:36.557
An angry branch
on last night's ride.

480
00:37:36.659 --> 00:37:39.027
May I?

481
00:37:39.128 --> 00:37:41.429
WILKIN:
In here. milady?

482
00:37:41.530 --> 00:37:43.064
LADY LOVE:
No better one

483
00:37:43.166 --> 00:37:45.466
to heal you than Him.

484
00:37:56.344 --> 00:37:58.712
The physicker
should look at this.

485
00:38:01.649 --> 00:38:06.053
(baby crying)

486
00:38:18.366 --> 00:38:20.767
I'll find the physicker.

487
00:38:20.868 --> 00:38:24.170
No. Stay.

488
00:38:24.271 --> 00:38:25.972
Finish your devotion.

489
00:38:26.073 --> 00:38:29.075
I'll have him find you.

490
00:38:55.435 --> 00:38:59.104
Baroness?

491
00:38:59.205 --> 00:39:02.307
I sent an emissary to London

492
00:39:02.409 --> 00:39:07.279
and one to Erik's brother
in Coventry.

493
00:39:07.381 --> 00:39:12.316
I'm sure our king will offer
comfort and guidance

494
00:39:12.418 --> 00:39:14.919
of how we proceed to govern.

495
00:39:15.020 --> 00:39:18.089
We proceed by
burying my husband.

496
00:39:19.324 --> 00:39:21.626
Yes.

497
00:39:21.727 --> 00:39:23.828
Of course.

498
00:39:26.998 --> 00:39:29.134
Another thought. milady.

499
00:39:30.535 --> 00:39:33.804
This executioner...

500
00:39:33.906 --> 00:39:35.773
his arrival.

501
00:39:35.874 --> 00:39:39.310
although it brought sadness...

502
00:39:39.411 --> 00:39:41.612
it could turn to good fortune.

503
00:39:41.713 --> 00:39:43.047
How so?

504
00:39:43.148 --> 00:39:45.616
If we secure him
and his soldier.

505
00:39:45.717 --> 00:39:48.619
we gain skilled men
to hunt offenders

506
00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:50.955
and carry out the correction.

507
00:39:51.056 --> 00:39:55.492
Sends a sound message.

508
00:39:55.593 --> 00:39:58.896
Ventrishire will not
suffer lawlessness.

509
00:40:01.766 --> 00:40:05.235
That's well advised.
dear Chamberlain.

510
00:40:05.336 --> 00:40:08.204
Good. I'll draft the letters

511
00:40:08.306 --> 00:40:10.607
that bind them.

512
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:33.729
I have news. Maddox.

513
00:40:35.332 --> 00:40:39.435
The trial was swift.
the guilt clear.

514
00:40:41.004 --> 00:40:43.439
We will stage the execution
in the village square

515
00:40:43.540 --> 00:40:45.842
midday tomorrow.

516
00:40:52.015 --> 00:40:54.683
He's your blood.

517
00:40:54.784 --> 00:40:57.119
There must be some...

518
00:40:57.220 --> 00:41:00.489
due leniency. a brother's mercy?

519
00:41:00.590 --> 00:41:02.858
You rid me of a mistake

520
00:41:02.959 --> 00:41:07.363
influenced by familial guilt.

521
00:41:09.032 --> 00:41:12.801
No kin. no worries.

522
00:41:14.670 --> 00:41:17.405
But of course.
you wouldn't understand that.

523
00:41:17.506 --> 00:41:21.075
Being a family man.

524
00:41:21.176 --> 00:41:24.178
And you're the final word
of justice here?

525
00:41:26.381 --> 00:41:29.684
As well as chancellor
and advisor.

526
00:41:29.785 --> 00:41:33.421
You'll find that nothing passes

527
00:41:33.522 --> 00:41:36.858
through this shire
without me touching it.

528
00:41:36.959 --> 00:41:39.293
I'm afraid that's a lesson
I'll have to miss.

529
00:41:39.394 --> 00:41:41.295
I move on after tomorrow.

530
00:41:41.396 --> 00:41:43.464
Ah. but that's my news.

531
00:41:43.565 --> 00:41:47.735
You and your soldier
will stay on.

532
00:41:47.836 --> 00:41:50.304
Your position is now standing.

533
00:41:54.876 --> 00:41:57.278
We're journeyman.

534
00:41:57.379 --> 00:41:59.146
Travelers.

535
00:41:59.248 --> 00:42:00.947
Now. you have a home.

536
00:42:01.048 --> 00:42:04.984
I'm sure that will be
a comfort to your

537
00:42:05.085 --> 00:42:08.054
wife and wee things.

538
00:42:11.859 --> 00:42:14.294
(breathing loudly)

539
00:42:21.935 --> 00:42:24.370
Why are you doing this?

540
00:42:27.039 --> 00:42:29.875
Our buried truths bind us.

541
00:42:29.976 --> 00:42:32.878
And your skills will serve me.

542
00:42:39.085 --> 00:42:41.487
I need a man

543
00:42:41.588 --> 00:42:43.889
with the heart of a dragon.

544
00:43:08.347 --> 00:43:10.748
(scratching)

545
00:43:12.984 --> 00:43:15.419
(soft gasp)

546
00:43:17.689 --> 00:43:20.124
ANNORA:
Ludwig?

547
00:43:31.803 --> 00:43:34.205
(shallow breathing)

548
00:43:47.685 --> 00:43:51.388
We need to ready our faith.

549
00:43:51.489 --> 00:43:56.259
(shakily):
<i>Ja. meine Liebe.</i>

550
00:44:02.367 --> 00:44:04.735
(breathing shakily)

551
00:44:21.640 --> 00:44:25.739
FATHER: <i>Dominus noster
Jesus Christus te absolvat</i>

552
00:44:25.774 --> 00:44:28.209
<i>Ego auctoritate</i>

553
00:44:28.410 --> 00:44:31.479
<i>ipsius te absolvo</i>

554
00:44:31.480 --> 00:44:35.749
<i>ab omni vinculo excommunicationis
et interdicti...</i>

555
00:44:35.850 --> 00:44:38.819
- (boys singing chant in Latin)
<i>- ...in quantum possum</i>

556
00:44:38.919 --> 00:44:41.755
<i>- et tu indiges.</i>
<i>- (groaning)</i>

557
00:44:41.856 --> 00:44:44.991
<i>Ego te absolvo</i>

558
00:44:45.092 --> 00:44:48.061
<i>a peccatis tuis</i>

559
00:44:48.162 --> 00:44:50.864
<i>in nomine Patris. et Filii.</i>

560
00:44:50.965 --> 00:44:52.631
<i>et Spiritus Sancti. Amen.</i>

561
00:44:57.437 --> 00:45:00.472
(Randulf groaning)

562
00:45:06.947 --> 00:45:09.347
(singing chant continues)

563
00:45:15.153 --> 00:45:17.521
Blades have been grinded. sir.

564
00:45:26.864 --> 00:45:29.199
(groans softly)

565
00:45:47.317 --> 00:45:49.752
(groans softly)

566
00:45:56.259 --> 00:45:58.627
(singing chant continues)

567
00:46:03.332 --> 00:46:06.134
(whispering. laughing)

568
00:46:06.235 --> 00:46:08.570
(inhales deeply)

569
00:46:08.671 --> 00:46:10.572
(exhales deeply)

570
00:46:10.673 --> 00:46:13.007
(quietly):
Help me.

571
00:46:16.311 --> 00:46:18.813
(crowd murmuring)

572
00:47:00.087 --> 00:47:03.723
Always.

573
00:47:18.238 --> 00:47:19.671
You'll need this. headsman.

574
00:47:19.772 --> 00:47:22.541
Little Rand was full of shit.

575
00:47:22.642 --> 00:47:24.443
(laughter)

576
00:47:24.544 --> 00:47:26.712
A stuffed clown.

577
00:47:26.812 --> 00:47:27.875
(laughter)

578
00:47:28.048 --> 00:47:29.449
You best take another.

579
00:47:29.550 --> 00:47:31.717
Yeah. His ass will spout
like a fountain.

580
00:47:31.818 --> 00:47:33.986
(laughter)

581
00:47:34.087 --> 00:47:35.521
Who did you spring from?

582
00:47:35.622 --> 00:47:37.690
(laughter)

583
00:48:02.248 --> 00:48:04.216
(yelling)

584
00:48:05.251 --> 00:48:07.052
(thudding)

585
